VB Fund Description

VB tracks the CRSP US Small Cap Index. The market-cap-weighted index includes the bottom 2-15% of the investable universe.

VB Factset Analytics Insight

VB is one of the giants in the small-cap space, as its broad index captures the US small-cap space well. VB earns high marks in Fit, in part a reflection of the fund's highly diverse portfolio. Note however that both the fund and our benchmark are skewed toward midcaps, so it could overlap with existing midcaps in your portfolio. (The fund switched to CRSP index in 2013.) VB is stable, with over a decade of trading history. The only negative mark here is one common to all Vanguard funds: holdings are reported monthly, not daily.

VB MSCI ESG Analytics Insight

Vanguard Small-Cap ETF has an MSCI ESG Fund Rating of BBB based on a score of 4.66 out of 10. The MSCI ESG Fund Rating measures the resiliency of portfolios to long-term risks and opportunities arising from environmental, social, and governance factors. ESG Fund Ratings range from best (AAA) to worst (CCC). Highly rated funds consist of companies that tend to show strong and/or improving management of financially relevant environmental, social and governance issues. These companies may be more resilient to disruptions arising from ESG events.

The funds Peer Rank reflects the ranking of a funds MSCI ESG Fund Quality Score against the scores of other funds within the same peer group, as defined by the Thomson Reuters Lipper Global Classification. Vanguard Small-Cap ETF ranks in the 25th percentile within its peer group and in the 38th percentile within the global universe of all funds covered by MSCI ESG Fund Ratings.
